1
00:00:00,750 --> 00:00:04,375
We were about 20 or more
people in the room, upstairs

2
00:00:04,666 --> 00:00:08,375
In this small room,
roughly three by four meters

3
00:00:10,666 --> 00:00:14,666
We sat next to each other,
leaning on one another

4
00:00:16,041 --> 00:00:17,083
We just sat there doing nothing

5
00:00:17,416 --> 00:00:23,666
Interviewer: Was there inside the room
mattresses or foam for sleeping and blankets?

6
00:00:23,791 --> 00:00:24,958
There was no foam

7
00:00:25,375 --> 00:00:27,666
The floor was just carpeted

8
00:00:28,500 --> 00:00:30,375
Interviewer: Carpeted with
what? Witness: With carpet

9
00:00:31,541 --> 00:00:34,125
Interviewer: You mean you
also entered without shoes?

10
00:00:35,083 --> 00:00:36,916
Yes, we took off our
shoes and entered

11
00:00:37,875 --> 00:00:43,250
Interviewer: Were there curtains
and windows in this room?

12
00:00:43,666 --> 00:00:47,958
All the windows were
closed and sealed with iron

13
00:00:47,958 --> 00:00:50,625
As you saw, they
were all sealed with iron

14
00:00:51,375 --> 00:00:54,166
There was only a small opening
that let in some light and air

15
00:00:54,958 --> 00:00:56,791
Interviewer: When
you entered this room

16
00:00:56,916 --> 00:00:59,791
Did you expect to find this
number of prisoners with you?

17
00:01:00,916 --> 00:01:01,916
No, I did not expect it

18
00:01:01,916 --> 00:01:04,166
When I entered, I was
shocked that this small room

19
00:01:04,250 --> 00:01:06,291
Had more than 20 people in it

20
00:01:07,041 --> 00:01:11,500
Can you imagine what the air would
be like from everyone breathing?

21
00:01:14,166 --> 00:01:16,541
Interviewer: What were
their approximate ages?

22
00:01:16,541 --> 00:01:19,375
From the youngest to the
oldest prisoner in this room

23
00:01:19,416 --> 00:01:22,375
And can you tell me what
exactly were their charges?

24
00:01:22,375 --> 00:01:23,875
Most of them were young men

25
00:01:23,916 --> 00:01:28,000
This one for smoking, that
one for being late to prayer

26
00:01:28,000 --> 00:01:30,083
That one for shaving his
beard, others for fighting

27
00:01:31,083 --> 00:01:32,750
They were of average young age

28
00:01:32,791 --> 00:01:37,250
And some were older,
about 30 or 35 or less

29
00:01:37,666 --> 00:01:39,291
Interviewer: You mean
there were no elderly people?

30
00:01:39,291 --> 00:01:40,625
No, there were no elderly people

31
00:01:41,000 --> 00:01:43,041
Interviewer: You mean the
oldest person was about 40?

32
00:01:43,041 --> 00:01:44,416
Yes, approximately
